0w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*PF000iS0UXq0ZlR6BrKPaw.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*PF000iS0UXq0ZlR6BrKPaw.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*PF000iS0UXq0ZlR6BrKPaw.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:934/1*PF000iS0UXq0ZlR6BrKPaw.png 934w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:467/1*PF000iS0UXq0ZlR6BrKPaw.png"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">Multiplying by 1 in the form of 3/3 turns 1/3 into the equivalent fraction 3/9</p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-7">fact five</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">Add and Subtract Equal Sized Parts</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">When adding and subtracting fractions <strong>the denominators must be the same</strong>. That makes sense. If we wish to combine or take away parts we must be talking about the same sized parts, otherwise it would get confusing.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><em>So what do you do if your fractions do not have the same sizes?</em></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
